HEADWORD: Dry nurse
<hw>Dry" nurse`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A nurse who attends and feeds a
child by hand; -- in distinction from a <contr>wet nurse</contr>, who
suckles it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>dry-nurse</ent>⟦br⟧
